  "text": "where M > 0 is the order of the AR channel process, (u n ) n∈Z is an i.i.d. driving process, and (a 1 , . . . , a M ) are the constant AR filter coefficients, which can be tuned to meet a required Doppler spectral density (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ). In the multipath case, this model can be generalized to account for the presence of a power delay profile and the presence of correlations between the channel taps in addition to the Doppler effect. In this case, the channel coefficients vector C n = [c n,0 , . . . , c n,L ] T is written as",
